The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 December is 123,127 (14,191.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 December, there were 5,589 new confirmed cases (644.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 5,659 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (70 fewer cases).
